WEBVTT

00:03.969 --> 00:05.445
Free Bobby to ride free!

00:05.469 --> 00:09.161
Free Bobby to ride free!
Free Bobby to ride free!

00:09.185 --> 00:10.796
Free Bobby to ride free!

00:10.820 --> 00:12.932
- Who's Bobby?
- He's their president.

00:12.956 --> 00:14.033
He's on trial in there for running

00:14.057 --> 00:15.634
a meth lab out of his garage.

00:15.658 --> 00:17.937
Bobby's riding five to seven,
what Bobby's riding.

00:17.961 --> 00:19.805
Back behind your bikes, guys!

00:19.829 --> 00:21.106
...free! Free Bobby to ride...

00:21.130 --> 00:23.609
It's a free country, Porky!

00:23.633 --> 00:25.811
- Back behind your bikes now.
- We got a right

00:25.835 --> 00:28.314
- to be heard!
- Behind your bikes, you do.

00:28.338 --> 00:31.106
Free Bobby to ride free!
Free Bobby to ride free!

00:32.442 --> 00:34.019
Hey! Hey! Hey, what's going on?

00:38.348 --> 00:40.326
I'm an uncle. I'm an uncle.

00:40.350 --> 00:41.727
Walsh, behind you!

00:49.692 --> 00:51.397
Where is Officer Janko?!

00:51.422 --> 00:52.867
Excuse me, ma'am, we're a little busy.

00:52.891 --> 00:55.148
- Please take a seat.
- I need to speak to her now.

00:55.173 --> 00:57.204
Ma'am, we're gonna have to
ask you to calm down, please.

00:57.228 --> 01:00.508
I'm not going to calm down until
you bring me Officer Janko.

01:00.532 --> 01:02.308
She's not here now. Maybe
I can help you with something?

01:02.332 --> 01:05.340
Yeah. You could start by explaining

01:05.340 --> 01:07.343
why I got a doctor

01:07.367 --> 01:10.022
badgering me and calling my house

01:10.046 --> 01:12.291
after my car accident last week.

01:12.315 --> 01:14.156
I'm sorry, what does this
have to do with Officer Janko?

01:14.180 --> 01:15.928
I was in a single-car crash.

01:15.952 --> 01:17.396
- Uh-huh.
- She's the only person

01:17.420 --> 01:19.731
that knows about this accident
besides me,

01:19.755 --> 01:21.633
and she filed a damn report.

01:21.657 --> 01:23.313
- Did you go to the hospital?
- No.

01:23.337 --> 01:25.604
- File a claim?
- I didn't even tell my husband,

01:25.628 --> 01:27.139
'cause I knew he'd have a fit.

01:27.163 --> 01:29.515
Look, I'm-I'm sure
it's probably a coincidence.

01:29.539 --> 01:32.311
I've read about cops
selling accident reports

01:32.335 --> 01:34.246
- like this before.
- I think you might

01:34.270 --> 01:35.581
be getting ahead of yourself.

01:35.605 --> 01:37.216
Here's the information.

01:37.240 --> 01:38.851
Dr. Mehta.

01:38.875 --> 01:40.986
Janko must have tipped off the doctor,

01:41.010 --> 01:42.577
who knows who else?

01:44.180 --> 01:45.657
All right.

01:45.681 --> 01:49.294
And you were alone in the store
when the robbers entered?

01:49.318 --> 01:51.486
I'm-I'm always the first one in.

01:52.855 --> 01:54.831
I thought the front door was locked

01:54.855 --> 01:57.169
when I opened up the safe
and started taking inventory

01:57.193 --> 01:59.805
of the jewels, but he entered,

01:59.829 --> 02:03.342
pulled the gun, pointed
it right at my face.

02:03.366 --> 02:06.411
And did he push you or hit you?

02:06.435 --> 02:09.383
No. He just said...

02:09.771 --> 02:12.387
"Call the cops and you're dead."

02:12.842 --> 02:16.144
So I just stood there and
watched him empty out the safe.

02:17.380 --> 02:19.447
Well, you did the smart thing.

02:20.483 --> 02:22.361
Can he find me?

02:23.065 --> 02:24.563
What do you mean?

02:24.587 --> 02:26.465
I-I don't know how this works.

02:26.489 --> 02:28.233
Is a crime report public?

02:28.257 --> 02:29.952
My name as a witness?

02:29.977 --> 02:32.322
No. Police report is not made public.

02:32.347 --> 02:33.847
So he can't, right?

02:37.567 --> 02:39.311
Full disclosure.

02:39.335 --> 02:42.214
A new fairness law
went into effect recently.

02:42.238 --> 02:45.117
It requires us to hand over
witnesses' contact information

02:45.141 --> 02:47.119
to the defense attorneys.

02:47.143 --> 02:48.598
You mean, like my address?

02:48.622 --> 02:50.932
Well, yes, but just to the attorneys.

02:50.957 --> 02:52.668
How is that fairness?

02:52.982 --> 02:55.460
I mean, what about
the witnesses, the victims?

02:55.484 --> 02:57.396
How-How's that fair to us?

02:57.933 --> 03:00.699
Katie, Goodman is in Rikers
until the trial.

03:00.723 --> 03:03.188
There is nothing to worry about.

03:10.399 --> 03:11.910
Ms. Hodge?

03:11.934 --> 03:13.579
I was in the building,

03:13.603 --> 03:15.681
thought I'd save myself a trip later.

03:15.705 --> 03:17.049
Goodman case files?

03:17.073 --> 03:18.951
Yes. It's been 15 days.

03:18.975 --> 03:20.516
You're now required by law

03:20.540 --> 03:22.162
to give over the witnesses' information.

03:22.187 --> 03:24.723
Actually, the law says
15 days from arraignment,

03:24.747 --> 03:26.325
so I have two more hours.

03:26.349 --> 03:28.327
So you're one of those.

03:28.351 --> 03:29.595
One of what?

03:29.619 --> 03:32.497
I just think it's a sin
to waste a colleague's time.

03:33.010 --> 03:35.400
I am happy to save you a trip.

03:36.154 --> 03:37.669
Do me a favor?

03:37.693 --> 03:40.439
Treat this like the loaded weapon it is.

03:40.463 --> 03:42.507
Kind of an overstatement.

03:42.531 --> 03:44.376
Well, maybe.

03:44.400 --> 03:47.679
But your client is
a repeat violent offender.

03:47.703 --> 03:50.849
So yes, the new law says I have
to hand over the contacts.

03:50.873 --> 03:52.818
It does not say you need to download

03:52.842 --> 03:54.847
all the names and addresses to him.

03:55.144 --> 03:56.460
I will do whatever I see fit

03:56.484 --> 03:59.162
to make sure that my client
receives a fair trial.

03:59.186 --> 04:00.699
I am sure you will.

04:00.699 --> 04:01.932
You have a good day.

04:02.786 --> 04:04.787
I will certainly try.

04:07.293 --> 04:09.271
And at 10:30 you are
meeting with Chief Kimura

04:09.296 --> 04:10.673
to review her proposal

04:10.698 --> 04:13.173
on new mental health
training initiatives.

04:13.288 --> 04:14.469
At 11:00...

04:14.493 --> 04:16.002
Push back my 11:00.

04:16.026 --> 04:18.173
I'm gonna need more time with Kimura.

04:18.197 --> 04:20.406
All right. So 11:30?

04:20.430 --> 04:22.888
- Good.
- Great. So at 11:30

04:22.888 --> 04:25.073
you will meet
with Chief Fitzgerald about...

04:25.098 --> 04:28.300
Could it wait five minutes?
We are almost done.

04:28.324 --> 04:30.613
Actually, no, it can't.

04:30.637 --> 04:33.082
A lawsuit's just been filed
against the department

04:33.106 --> 04:35.734
claiming excessive force
was used during an arrest.

04:35.734 --> 04:38.169
So? We get those complaints all the time.

04:40.172 --> 04:42.550
The plaintiff is an NYPD detective

04:42.574 --> 04:45.476
who's been deep undercover
the last nine months.

04:48.352 --> 04:49.943
Our officer

04:49.967 --> 04:53.217
didn't know he was
taking down a fellow cop.

04:58.523 --> 04:59.834
What do we got?

04:59.858 --> 05:01.676
Vic is a white male in his 50s

05:01.676 --> 05:03.054
found this morning by a jogger.

05:03.078 --> 05:05.223
Wife, kids and the nanny were
asleep up their apartment.

05:05.247 --> 05:06.691
His name is Felix Roth.

05:06.715 --> 05:08.559
- Like the photographer?
- Beats me.

05:08.583 --> 05:11.295
His wife's upstairs... you can
ask her if he takes pictures.

05:11.319 --> 05:12.363
You think?

05:12.387 --> 05:13.698
We got it from here.

05:13.722 --> 05:15.500
Danny, this guy's been all over the news

05:15.524 --> 05:16.868
the past couple of weeks.

05:16.892 --> 05:18.603
- What'd he do?
- Well, more like

05:18.627 --> 05:19.737
what didn't he do?

05:19.761 --> 05:21.239
A ton of his former models

05:21.263 --> 05:22.807
came forward claiming sexual assault.

05:22.831 --> 05:24.509
It's up to, like, 20 now,

05:24.533 --> 05:27.868
- and counting. Real nasty stuff, too.
- Really?

05:28.904 --> 05:31.572
So 'twas beauty killed the beast.

